Diagnosis
. One of the smaller species in this genus (6.9–9.0 mm long). Dorsal surface very pale brown, often very pale greyish in more recently collected specimens; dark marking at elytral apex if present may be difficult to discern from above (
Fig. 21
); with either one (as in 
type
; 
Fig. 22
) or two dark coloured abdominal ventrites anterior to light organs; apex of sheath sternite emarginated on right side, and the prolonged median anterior margin of the sheath tergite relatively short and apically narrowed (
Figs 32−35
).
